&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Care Organisation: &lt;/strong&gt;Bury and Rochdale Care Organisation; based at &lt;span&gt;Rochdale Infirmary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Bury &amp; Rochdale Care Organisation includes Fairfield General Hospital, Rochdale Infirmary and the Integrated Community Services of Heywood, Middleton and Rochdale. There are eight directorates within the CO;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-HMR Urgent Care and Intermediate Tier Services Directorate (Rochdale)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-HMR Integrated Neighbourhood Teams Directorate (Rochdale)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Emergency &amp; Urgent Care Directorate (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-General &amp; Specialist Medicine Directorate (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Elective Orthopaedic &amp; ENT Directorate (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Gastroenterology Directorate (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Clinical Support Services (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Ophthalmology Directorate (Bury)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity has arisen for an experienced and proactive Consultant to join our busy and dynamic team at Rochdale Infirmary covering the areas of Acute Medicine on the Clinical Assessment Unit and Oasis Units, and SDEC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic candidates with ambition and vision to join our team. You should be a team player with a strong clinical background. The successful candidate will have the opportunity to help lead service developments and develop clinical leadership across the Health and Social Care System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
